{"TopicId":217763,"ForumId":34,"TopicTitle":"[1.12.5] janellie\u0027s Gimbal Trim - Manual thrust vectoring","CreatedByName":"janellie82","CreatedById":229469,"CreatedDateTime":"2023-06-18T21:20:30Z","PageNum":1,"Articles":[{"CreatedByName":"janellie82","CreatedById":229469,"CreatedDateTime":"2023-06-18T21:20:30Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp style=\u0022text-align:center;\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cspan style=\u0022font-size:20px;\u0022\u003E\u003Cstrong\u003Ejanellie\u0027s GimbalTrim\u003C/strong\u003E\u003C/span\u003E\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp style=\u0022text-align:center;\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cimg alt=\u0022hhGVniI.png\u0022 class=\u0022ipsImage\u0022 data-ratio=\u002270.87\u0022 height=\u0022652\u0022 width=\u0022920\u0022 src=\u0022https://i.imgur.com/hhGVniI.png\u0022\u003E\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nA small KSP mod that allows the player to manually adjust an engine\u0027s gimbal.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u003Cstrong\u003ERequires \u003Ca href=\u0022https://forum.kerbalspaceprogram.com/topic/50533-18x-112x-module-manager-422-june-18th-2022-the-heatwave-edition/\u0022 rel=\u0022\u0022\u003EModuleManager\u003C/a\u003E\u003C/strong\u003E\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nSome notes:\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cul\u003E\n\u003Cli\u003E\nPilot input and \u003Cabbr title=\u0022Stability Augmentation System\u0022\u003E\u003Cabbr title=\u0022Stability Augmentation System\u0022\u003ESAS\u003C/abbr\u003E\u003C/abbr\u003E can\u0027t control the engine\u0027s gimbal while trim is active.\n\u003C/li\u003E\n\u003Cli\u003E\nGimbal trim is limited by the engine\u0027s gimbal range as given in the engine\u0027s config file, but limiting the vectoring range in-game doesn\u0027t affect trim, only \u003Cabbr title=\u0022Stability Augmentation System\u0022\u003E\u003Cabbr title=\u0022Stability Augmentation System\u0022\u003ESAS\u003C/abbr\u003E\u003C/abbr\u003E/pilot input.\n\u003C/li\u003E\n\u003Cli\u003E\nTrim can only be used if the vessel is under full control (i.e. has a pilot onboard or has a connection to \u003Cabbr title=\u0022Kerbal Space Center\u0022\u003E\u003Cabbr title=\u0022Kerbal Space Center\u0022\u003EKSC\u003C/abbr\u003E\u003C/abbr\u003E).\n\u003C/li\u003E\n\u003Cli\u003E\nUnlike all the other stock\u002BDLC engines, the Bobcat from Making History has two gimbal modules; this mod can only control the left one.\n\u003C/li\u003E\n\u003C/ul\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nDownload from \u003Ca href=\u0022https://spacedock.info/mod/3408/Gimbal%20Trim\u0022 rel=\u0022external nofollow\u0022\u003ESpacedock\u003C/a\u003E\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nSource on \u003Ca href=\u0022https://github.com/janellie82/GimbalTrim\u0022 rel=\u0022external nofollow\u0022\u003EGitHub\u003C/a\u003E\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nDistributed under the CC-BY-4.0 license.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cspan class=\u0022ipsType_reset ipsType_medium ipsType_light\u0022 data-excludequote=\u0022\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cstrong\u003EEdited \u003Ctime datetime=\u00222024-05-17T02:49:35Z\u0022 title=\u002205/17/2024 02:49  AM\u0022 data-short=\u0022May 17\u0022\u003EMay 17\u003C/time\u003E by janellie82\u003C/strong\u003E\n\u003C/span\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"kurgut","CreatedById":188918,"CreatedDateTime":"2023-06-19T08:06:39Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003E\nThank you for this ! \u003Cspan\u003E\u003Cimg alt=\u0022:)\u0022 data-emoticon=\u0022\u0022 src=\u0022//kerbal-forum-uploads.s3.us-west-2.amazonaws.com/emoticons/default_k_smiley.gif\u0022 title=\u0022:)\u0022\u003E\u00A0\u003C/span\u003E\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u003Cspan\u003EDoes that mean I could eventually map the X and Y gimbal axis to action groups incremental controls ?\u003C/span\u003E\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u003Cspan\u003EPeace\u003C/span\u003E\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"janellie82","CreatedById":229469,"CreatedDateTime":"2023-06-19T17:40:24Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003E\nNew release:\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n1.1.0 - Gimbal X and Gimbal Y now respond correctly to action group axes and KAL controllers\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u00A0\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cblockquote class=\u0022ipsQuote\u0022 data-ipsquote=\u0022\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentapp=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentclass=\u0022forums_Topic\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentcommentid=\u00224294455\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentid=\u0022217763\u0022 data-ipsquote-contenttype=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-timestamp=\u00221687161999\u0022 data-ipsquote-userid=\u0022188918\u0022 data-ipsquote-username=\u0022kurgut\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_citation\u0022\u003E\n9 hours ago, kurgut said:\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_contents\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u003Cspan\u003EDoes that mean I could eventually map the X and Y gimbal axis to action groups incremental controls ?\u003C/span\u003E\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/blockquote\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nWith the latest patch, yes.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"kurgut","CreatedById":188918,"CreatedDateTime":"2023-06-19T18:42:30Z","Content":"\n\u003Cblockquote class=\u0022ipsQuote\u0022 data-ipsquote=\u0022\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentapp=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentclass=\u0022forums_Topic\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentcommentid=\u00224294554\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentid=\u0022217763\u0022 data-ipsquote-contenttype=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-timestamp=\u00221687196424\u0022 data-ipsquote-userid=\u0022229469\u0022 data-ipsquote-username=\u0022janellie82\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_citation\u0022\u003E\n1 hour ago, janellie82 said:\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_contents\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nWith the latest patch, yes.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/blockquote\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nperfect thanks ! this opens new opportunities\u00A0\u003Cspan\u003E\u003Cspan\u003E\u003Cimg alt=\u0022:)\u0022 data-emoticon=\u0022\u0022 src=\u0022//kerbal-forum-uploads.s3.us-west-2.amazonaws.com/emoticons/default_k_smiley.gif\u0022 title=\u0022:)\u0022\u003E\u00A0\u003C/span\u003E\u003C/span\u003E\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"septemberWaves","CreatedById":160814,"CreatedDateTime":"2023-06-20T07:24:42Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003E\nWhat would be the practical use case of this?\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"jebediahs_internet_account","CreatedById":229179,"CreatedDateTime":"2023-06-20T18:09:27Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003E\nYou can set up a KAL controller or kOS script to smoothly move the gimbal as the \u003Cabbr title=\u0022Center of Mass\u0022\u003ECoM\u003C/abbr\u003E moves in a space shuttle, for example.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"TruthfulGnome","CreatedById":205487,"CreatedDateTime":"2023-06-29T05:37:33Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003E\nThank you for this! been needing something like this for ages, absolutely perfect.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"janellie82","CreatedById":229469,"CreatedDateTime":"2024-05-17T02:53:09Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003E\nNew release:\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n1.2.0 - Added localization support and a Russian translation. The mod only has 4 lines and less than 10 words, so if you wish to add your translation, contact me.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"}]}